  <description type="morphology">Caudex usually simple. Stems usually few from base, erect or outer decumbent, 1.5–2.5 dm. Basal leaves: blade (outer) often broadly elliptic, base narrowing gradually to petiole, margins sinuate to dentate (or blade deltate, less than 1 cm, base abruptly narrowed to petiole). Racemes usually elongated. Petals white, (9–)11–15 mm, often 2 times as long as sepals. 2n = 12.</description>
  <description type="phenology">Flowering Mar-May, usually in Apr.</description>
  <description type="habitat">Limey and gravelly knolls, grassland hills, limestone hillsides and breaks, gypsum, shale, rocky calcareous soils, stony areas, prairie pastures, limestone roadcuts;</description>
  <description type="elevation">150-700 m;</description>
  <description type="distribution">Kans., Okla.</description>
